org.safs.model.examples.advanced

Class JSAFSMap.LoginWindow

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.safs.model.examples.advanced.JSAFSMap.LoginWindow
  • Enclosing class:
    JSAFSMap

    public static class JSAFSMap.LoginWindow
extends java.lang.Object
    Easy-to-use access to LoginWindow Component names and types. Each of the Component types mapped to a named component is expected to match the type of component as it is mapped in the real runtime SAFS App Map(s). In this way, the references stored here can be used directly in Driver calls requiring a reference to ComponentFunction components.

    Mappings like this allow a Driver test to perform actions using syntax shown below:

      result = jsafs.runComponentFunction(JSAFSMap.LoginWindow.Submit.click());

    See Also:
    JSAFSDriver.runComponentFunction(org.safs.model.ComponentFunction)
